# PROCESS_DOCUMENTS schedule used by go-crond.
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - If you change this cron expression in the deployment config map, also update
#   EXTRACTION_QUEUE_CRON_INTERVAL_MINUTES in both:
#     1. condition-cron config/env
#     2. condition-api config/env
# - The web UI uses EXTRACTION_QUEUE_CRON_INTERVAL_MINUTES to estimate when the
#   next queued document will start processing.
# - Keep these values aligned manually. The app no longer rewrites this file at
#   container startup.
#
# Example:
# - `*/30 * * * *` means every 30 minutes, so use
#   EXTRACTION_QUEUE_CRON_INTERVAL_MINUTES=30
# - `0 * * * *` means every 60 minutes, so use
#   EXTRACTION_QUEUE_CRON_INTERVAL_MINUTES=60
*/30 * * * * default cd /condition-cron && ./run_process_documents.sh
